es after the publication of Torremuzza 1769",1769,1800,[68,73],{"_":69,"type":70,"ref":71,"region":72},"Drepanum","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462187","Sicilia",{"_":74,"type":75,"ref":76,"region":72},"Trapani","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2522876",[78],[79,80],38.0176,12.53617,{"_":82,"type":83,"subtype":84,"geo":20},"Reportedly found in 1768 during work on the Chiesa di San Pietro, Trapani","found","discovered",[],{"_":87,"type":88,"subtype":89,"geo":20},"None","observed","autopsied",{"_":91,"type":92,"subtype":93,"geo":20},"Lost.","not-observed","lost",[95],{"n":96,"url":97,"height":98,"width":99,"desc":100,"surfaceType":101},"screen","ISic003549_tiled.tif","3680px","5520px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana","front","Sicily",{"_":104,"role":105,"ref":106,"museum":107},"Museo Regionale Agostino Pepoli","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/105",{"slug":108,"type":105,"name":104,"uri":106,"description":109,"location":110},"105","The archaeological collection is housed in one long room that has been subdivided into 4 discrete areas containing 25 cases and a series of open displays. 1 case contains pre- and proto-historic material, 3 are for material from Selinunte, 1 Camarina, 8 Erice, 1 Mozia, 1 Birgi, 1 Lilybaeum, 1 Centuripe, 4 contain material of unknown origin, 1 mixed sites, and then 1 for Punic stamped amphora handles, 1 for Greek and Roman stamped amphora handles, and 1 for Latin epigraphy. In addition there are open displays of material found on the seabed (amphorae, anchor parts, a Roman ram from the Aegadi Islands battle), a large two-sided Latin inscription and a section on Arabic and later Jewish inscriptions",{"settlement":74,"region":74,"country":111,"address":112,"geo":113},"Italy","Via Conte A. Pepoli 180. 91100 - Trapani (TP)",{"lat":114,"lon":115},38.01913,12.541978,[117,120],{"_":118,"typ