ΑΡΧΗΓΕΤΕΙἈρχηγέτει | l.2 reg., orig. εὐαπσεστάτωα\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"ἈρχηγέτειἈρχηγέτηι εὐχὴ Ἡρακλεῖ Θαλλοφόρῳ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"epithet\" data-text=\"ἈρχηγέτειἈρχηγέτηι\">ΑΡΧΗΓΕΤΕΙ\u003C/span>ΕΥΧΗ\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἡρακλεῖ\">ΗΡΑΚΛΕΙ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"epithet\" data-text=\"Θαλλοφόρῳ\">ΘΑΛΛΟΦΟΡΩ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΙΕΡΩΕΥΑΠΣΕΣΤΑΤΩΑ\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Λούκιος Κορνήλιος Λουκίου\n                    Κορνηλίου υἱὸς ΠΑΝ Τερεντιανὸς\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Λούκιος\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Κορνήλιος\">ΚΟΡΝΗΛΙΟΣ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Λουκίου\n                    Κορνηλίου\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Λουκίου\">Λ\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Κορνηλίου\">ΚΟΡΝΗΛΙΟΥ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>ΥΙΟΣΠΑΝ\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Τερεντιανὸς\">ΤΕΡΕΝΤΙΑΝΟΣ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΚΑΙ\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Λήμνιος\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Λήμνιος\">ΛΗΜΝΙΟΣ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>ΑΠΕΛΕΥΘΕΡΟΣΕΠΟΙΗΣΑΝ\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ΠΠ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.1 reg., orig. ΑΡΧΗΓΕΤΕΙἈρχηγέτει | l.2 reg., orig. εὐαπσεστάτωα\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003549_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003549_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003549.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003549-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on comparison of Kaibel, Filippi and SEG, prioritising Kaibel's transcription of the manuscript tradition.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"3\">3: \u003Cspan>ΠΑΝ: perhaps for either Γαλ(ερια) Παλ(ατινα) (so Tybout, ap. SEG)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"5\">5: \u003Cspan>ΠΠ: perhaps for p(ecunia) p(osuit) or p(ropria) p(ecunia) (so Tybout, ap. SEG)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>As Korhonen lucidly details, the inscription is one of a series of late 18th century local antiquarian forgeries, constructed on the basis of existing texts, principally those to be found in the 1769 first edition of the corpus of Torremuzza. In the specific case of this inscription, De Bernardin noted this already in 2012. Kaibel classed the entire series already as forgeries in IG XIV.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 52.0894 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> 62.0654 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">30*\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Filippi 2002 73 no. 15/5 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001991\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001991\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Filippi 2005 69 no. 15/5 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002296\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002296\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> De Bernardin 2012 307-308 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002297\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002297\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2017 198 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001484\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001484\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\"> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[254,257,260,263,266,269,272,275],{"id":255,"html":256},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id